People have been warned to keep away from Salmon Grove, 407 Alton Lembede Street after reports emerged that a Government Employment Fund Employee (GEPF) is allegedly holding people hostage. The drama apparently unfolded from about 3 pm on Thursday, 10 May . According to Emer-G-Med Paramedics, who were on the scene along with various law enforcement agencies, it is an active hostage situation. “At this stage the scene is under the control of the South African Police Services and paramedics remain on standby should they be required,” said a statement from Emer- G-Med. Provincial police spokesperson Colonel Thembeka Mbele said she would only be able to confirm the incident when she got to the scene.